The paper discusses the use of deep neural networks for pattern recognition tasks, specifically in the context of vision classification problems. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on understanding the inner workings of neural networks, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The use of activation maximization and deep generator networks also suggests a focus on neural networks and their architecture, which could place the paper in the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the interpretability of the features learned by each neuron, which could place it in the natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-category.
